author: BRIAN ROKOS
title: RIVERSIDE: Man killed in 91 freeway crash is identified
text:
By BRIAN ROKOS / STAFF WRITER
Published: Oct. 5, 2015 7:39 a.m. RIVERSIDE: Man killed in 91 freeway crash is identified Print Photo Share Pin It More Galleries ADVERTISEMENT Timothy Fitzpatrick Jr., 31, was killed when the SUV he was driving overturned on the 91 freeway in Riverside on Oct. 4, 2015. COURTESY OF RIVERSIDE FIRE DEPARTMENT Related article Â» The man who died when he was thrown from the SUV he was driving on the 91 freeway in Riverside was identified Monday, Oct. 5, as Timothy Fitzpatrick Jr., 31, of Riverside.
The crash happened at 12:50 p.m. Sunday in the eastbound lanes, west of Adams Street. Fitzpatrick was pronounced dead at 1:02 p.m., the Riverside County Coroner's Office said.
A witness told authorities that the driver attempted to pass a car, overcompensated and overturned, according to a California Highway Patrol incident log.
